The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, August 12, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Calcutta, Aug. 11: Ruia-controlled Essar Steel has decided to write off its accumulated losses of Rs 1,356.30 crore as on March 31, 2004 by utilising funds lying with the securities premium account. The decision was part of an internal financial restructuring, which would result in the right sizing of the balance sheet, official sources said. The shareholders have already approved the proposal. The SPA would be reduced to Rs 39.88 crore with the proposed set off from Rs 1418.56 crore as on March 31.																								 Mumbai, Aug. 11: ICICI Bank will raise $300 million through issuance of Eurobonds in the international markets as the first tranche of its $1-billion medium term notes programme.																								 Mumbai, Aug. 11: Centurion Bank Limited today said its rights issue, aggregating Rs 90.8 crore, will open on August 24. The bank will offer shareholders two shares for every five held, at a price of Rs 4 per share.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 11: R. S. P. Sinha has been appointed chairman and managing director of Mahanagar Telephone Nigam.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 11: The ministry of commerce will hold discussions with the Planning Commission and the agriculture ministry on the strategy for post-WTO framework negotiations. 
